※※
# rename-sky-workflow

Manually-run workflow that renames a `.sky` file atomically: it `git mv`s the file,
fixes its `⊕meta⊕ name =` field, and rewrites `skyway run <old>` references across the
library — behind a manual gate — then lints the result and verifies the old name is
gone. Pure bash, no LLM tokens.

  (manual run: --var dir, name, new-name)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  not found ──▶ list <dir> + stop
   │  find  │  shows old->new + `skyway run <old>` ref hits
   └────────┘
       │ found
       ▼
   ┌─────────┐  reject ──▶ stop (nothing changed)
   │ confirm │  ⏸ manual approval gate (timeout 1h)
   └─────────┘
       │ approve
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  git mv + fix name= + rewrite `skyway run <old>`
   │ apply  │
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  skyway lint new file; warn on leftover old refs
   │ verify │
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
     done

Run it (state where the workflow lives with --var dir):

  skyway run rename-sky-workflow \
    --var dir=".sky/workflows" \
    --var name="old-name" \
    --var new-name="new-name"

  - dir       directory the workflow lives in — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)
  - name      current kebab-case filename (no .sky extension)
  - new-name  new kebab-case filename + workflow name (no .sky extension)

Scope note: the reference rewrite targets `skyway run <old>` occurrences. It does a
plain text replace, so if one workflow name is a prefix of another the verify step
flags any leftover for manual review. It does not touch `sky_event` names (those are
event identifiers, not workflow names).
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "rename-sky-workflow"
description = "Atomically rename a .sky: git mv, fix its meta name, rewrite `skyway run <old>` refs behind a manual gate, then lint and verify. Fire via: skyway run rename-sky-workflow --var dir=<dir> --var name=<old> --var new-name=<new>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※find※
Step 1 — find. Resolves the source file, refuses if the target name already exists,
and prints every `skyway run <old>` reference that the apply step will rewrite.
※※

§find§
bash_file = "./scripts/find.sh"
§§

※confirm※
Step 2 — confirm. depends_on=[find]. Manual gate: human approves rename + rewrite; reject to stop; timeout 1h.
※※

§confirm§
depends_on = ["find"]
wait.prompt = "Rename {{name}} -> {{new-name}} in {{dir}} and rewrite `skyway run {{name}}` references? Approve to apply."
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※apply※
Step 3 — apply. depends_on=[confirm]. git mv file, fix name= field, text-replace `skyway run <old>` -> `skyway run <new>` across dir; uses sed.
※※

§apply§
depends_on = ["confirm"]
bash_file = "./scripts/apply.sh"
§§

※verify※
Step 4 — verify. depends_on=[apply]. Lint renamed file (catches name<->filename mismatch); warn on leftover `skyway run <old>` refs.
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["apply"]
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
§§
